{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-03",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_03_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "03 - A Caucus-race and a Long Tale",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 1.54,
  "page_num": 1,
  "page_total": 3,
  "page_start_sec": 8.27,
  "page_end_sec": 254.28,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 8.27,
      "end": 9.12,
      "text": "CHAPTER III."
    },
    {
      "start": 9.12,
      "end": 11.18,
      "text": "A CAUCUS-RACE AND A LONG TALE."
    },
    {
      "start": 12.94,
      "end": 17.82,
      "text": " They were indeed a queer-looking party that assembled on the bank--the birds with draggled",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 17.82,
      "end": 22.94,
      "text": " feathers, the animals with their fur clinging close to them, and all dripping wet, cross,"
    },
    {
      "start": 23.16,
      "end": 23.82,
      "text": " and uncomfortable."
    },
    {
      "start": 24.72,
      "end": 27.58,
      "text": " The first question of course was, how to get dry again: they had a"
    },
    {
      "start": 27.58,
      "end": 30.96,
      "text": " consultation about this, and after a few minutes"
    },
    {
      "start": 30.0,
      "end": 32.3,
      "text": "it seemed quite natural to"
    },
    {
      "start": 32.3,
      "end": 34.7,
      "text": "Alice to find herself talking familiarly with"
    },
    {
      "start": 34.7,
      "end": 34.92,
      "text": "them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 35.02,
      "end": 36.88,
      "text": "as if she had known them all her life."
    },
    {
      "start": 37.12,
      "end": 37.22,
      "text": "Indeed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 37.9,
      "end": 39.74,
      "text": "she had quite a long argument with the"
    },
    {
      "start": 39.84,
      "end": 40.0,
      "text": "Lory,"
    },
    {
      "start": 40.18,
      "end": 42.28,
      "text": "who at last turned sulky, and would only say,"
    },
    {
      "start": 42.42,
      "end": 43.8,
      "text": "\"I am older than you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 43.96,
      "end": 44.8,
      "text": "and must know better;\""
    },
    {
      "start": 45.9,
      "end": 48.88,
      "text": "and this Alice would not allow without knowing how old it was,"
    },
    {
      "start": 49.1,
      "end": 50.48,
      "text": "and, as the Lory positively"
    },
    {
      "start": 50.84,
      "end": 52.02,
      "text": "refused to tell its age,"
    },
    {
      "start": 52.22,
      "end": 53.4,
      "text": "there was no more to be said."
    },
    {
      "start": 54.72,
      "end": 55.66,
      "text": "At last the Mouse,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 55.76,
      "end": 56.5,
      "text": "who seemed to be a"
    },
    {
      "start": 56.62,
      "end": 58.06,
      "text": "person of authority among them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 58.16,
      "end": 58.76,
      "text": "called out,"
    },
    {
      "start": 58.86,
      "end": 59.44,
      "text": "\"Sit down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 59.58,
      "end": 60.06,
      "text": "all of you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 60.1,
      "end": 60.76,
      "text": "and listen to me!"
    },
    {
      "start": 60.94,
      "end": 61.7,
      "text": "_I'll_ soon"
    },
    {
      "start": 61.76,
      "end": 62.74,
      "text": "make you dry enough!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 63.31,
      "end": 65.06,
      "text": "They all sat down at once,"
    },
    {
      "start": 65.14,
      "end": 65.86,
      "text": "in a large ring,"
    },
    {
      "start": 66.02,
      "end": 67.08,
      "text": "with the Mouse in the middle."
    },
    {
      "start": 67.872,
      "end": 69.9,
      "text": "Alice kept her eyes anxiously fixed on it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 69.94,
      "end": 72.26,
      "text": "for she felt sure she would catch a bad cold if she"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.26,
      "end": 73.58,
      "text": "did not get dry very soon."
    },
    {
      "start": 74.48,
      "end": 74.9,
      "text": "\"Ahem!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 75.1,
      "end": 76.92,
      "text": "said the Mouse with an important air."
    },
    {
      "start": 77.96,
      "end": 78.56,
      "text": "\"Are you all ready?"
    },
    {
      "start": 78.74,
      "end": 78.848,
      "text": "This"
    },
    {
      "start": 79.5,
      "end": 81.04,
      "text": "is the driest thing I know."
    },
    {
      "start": 81.3,
      "end": 82.48,
      "text": "Silence all round,"
    },
    {
      "start": 82.52,
      "end": 83.04,
      "text": "if you please!"
    },
    {
      "start": 85.024,
      "end": 86.24,
      "text": "'William the Conqueror,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 86.26,
      "end": 86.88,
      "text": "whose cause"
    },
    {
      "start": 86.88,
      "end": 88.28,
      "text": "was favoured by the pope,"
    },
    {
      "start": 88.48,
      "end": 90.88,
      "text": "was soon submitted to by the English,"
    },
    {
      "start": 91.26,
      "end": 92.04,
      "text": "who wanted leaders,"
    },
    {
      "start": 92.34,
      "end": 93.0,
      "text": "and had been"
    },
    {
      "start": 93.0,
      "end": 95.7,
      "text": "of late much accustomed to usurpation and conquest."
    },
    {
      "start": 96.768,
      "end": 97.58,
      "text": "Edwin and Morcar,'"
    },
    {
      "start": 97.8,
      "end": 99.78,
      "text": "the earls of Mercia and Northumbria--'"
    },
    {
      "start": 100.3,
      "end": 100.54,
      "text": "\"Ugh!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 100.54,
      "end": 100.86,
      "text": "said the Lory,"
    },
    {
      "start": 101.02,
      "end": 102.6,
      "text": "with a shiver.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 103.5,
      "end": 104.98,
      "text": "\"I beg your pardon!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 105.16,
      "end": 105.8,
      "text": "said the Mouse,"
    },
    {
      "start": 105.92,
      "end": 107.26,
      "text": "frowning, but very politely."
    },
    {
      "start": 107.34,
      "end": 108.16,
      "text": "\"Did you speak?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 109.152,
      "end": 109.48,
      "text": "\"Not I!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 109.84,
      "end": 111.02,
      "text": "said the Lory hastily.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 111.78,
      "end": 112.92,
      "text": "\"I thought you did,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 113.14,
      "end": 113.66,
      "text": "said the Mouse."
    },
    {
      "start": 114.38,
      "end": 114.76,
      "text": "\"--I proceed."
    },
    {
      "start": 116.096,
      "end": 117.1,
      "text": "'Edwin and Morcar,"
    },
    {
      "start": 117.22,
      "end": 119.32,
      "text": "the earls of Mercia and Northumbria,"
    },
    {
      "start": 119.46,
      "end": 120.3,
      "text": "declared for him:"
    },
    {
      "start": 120.7,
      "end": 121.78,
      "text": "and even Stigand,"
    },
    {
      "start": 121.8,
      "end": 124.0,
      "text": "the patriotic Archbishop of Canterbury,"
    },
    {
      "start": 124.18,
      "end": 125.06,
      "text": "found it advisable--'"
    },
    {
      "start": 125.92,
      "end": 126.32,
      "text": "\"Found _what_?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 126.56,
      "end": 127.2,
      "text": "said the Duck.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 128.0,
      "end": 128.34,
      "text": "\"Found _it_,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 128.56,
      "end": 130.12,
      "text": "the Mouse replied rather crossly:"
    },
    {
      "start": 130.2,
      "end": 131.0,
      "text": "\"of course you know what"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.16,
      "end": 131.56,
      "text": "'it' means.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 132.58,
      "end": 135.68,
      "text": "\"I know what 'it' means well enough, when _I_ find a thing,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 135.9,
      "end": 136.48,
      "text": "said the Duck;"
    },
    {
      "start": 136.62,
      "end": 138.3,
      "text": "\"it's generally a frog"
    },
    {
      "start": 138.54,
      "end": 139.16,
      "text": "or a worm."
    },
    {
      "start": 139.38,
      "end": 140.34,
      "text": "The question is,"
    },
    {
      "start": 140.44,
      "end": 141.98,
      "text": "what did the archbishop find?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 143.14,
      "end": 144.72,
      "text": "The Mouse did not notice this question,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 144.94,
      "end": 146.02,
      "text": "but hurriedly went on,"
    },
    {
      "start": 146.848,
      "end": 148.96,
      "text": "'--found it advisable to go with Edgar"
    },
    {
      "start": 148.96,
      "end": 151.06,
      "text": "Atheling to meet William and offer him"
    },
    {
      "start": 151.06,
      "end": 151.48,
      "text": "the crown."
    },
    {
      "start": 151.82,
      "end": 154.34,
      "text": "William's conduct at first was moderate."
    },
    {
      "start": 155.08,
      "end": 156.75,
      "text": "But the insolence of his Normans--'"
    },
    {
      "start": 157.22,
      "end": 158.24,
      "text": "\"How are you getting on now,"
    },
    {
      "start": 158.34,
      "end": 158.72,
      "text": "my dear?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 159.3,
      "end": 161.32,
      "text": "it continued, turning to Alice as it spoke."
    },
    {
      "start": 162.5,
      "end": 163.3,
      "text": "\"As wet as ever,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 163.44,
      "end": 165.1,
      "text": "said Alice in a melancholy tone;"
    },
    {
      "start": 165.39,
      "end": 167.24,
      "text": "\"doesn't seem to dry me at all.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 168.82,
      "end": 169.55,
      "text": "\"In that case,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 169.78,
      "end": 171.3,
      "text": "said the Dodo solemnly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 171.3,
      "end": 172.2,
      "text": "rising to its feet,"
    },
    {
      "start": 172.64,
      "end": 175.08,
      "text": "\"I move that the meeting adjourn, for the"
    },
    {
      "start": 175.08,
      "end": 177.84,
      "text": "immediate adoption of more energetic remedies----\""
    },
    {
      "start": 179.872,
      "end": 180.68,
      "text": "\"Speak English!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 180.92,
      "end": 181.72,
      "text": "said the Eaglet."
    },
    {
      "start": 182.3,
      "end": 185.16,
      "text": "\"I don't know the meaning of half those long words,"
    },
    {
      "start": 185.22,
      "end": 185.74,
      "text": "and, what's more,"
    },
    {
      "start": 185.82,
      "end": 187.46,
      "text": "I don't believe you do either!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 188.58,
      "end": 191.08,
      "text": "And the Eaglet bent down its head to hide a smile:"
    },
    {
      "start": 191.28,
      "end": 193.14,
      "text": "some of the other birds tittered audibly."
    },
    {
      "start": 194.96,
      "end": 196.24,
      "text": "\"What I was going to say,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 196.46,
      "end": 198.34,
      "text": "said the Dodo in an offended tone,"
    },
    {
      "start": 199.36,
      "end": 202.92,
      "text": "\"was that the best thing to get us dry would be a Caucus-race.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 204.96,
      "end": 205.98,
      "text": "\"What _is_ a Caucus-race?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 206.2,
      "end": 206.76,
      "text": "said Alice;"
    },
    {
      "start": 206.94,
      "end": 208.46,
      "text": "not that she much wanted to know,"
    },
    {
      "start": 208.64,
      "end": 210.52,
      "text": "but the Dodo had paused as if it"
    },
    {
      "start": 210.52,
      "end": 212.1,
      "text": "thought that _somebody_ ought to speak,"
    },
    {
      "start": 212.24,
      "end": 213.46,
      "text": "and no one else seemed"
    },
    {
      "start": 213.6,
      "end": 214.6,
      "text": "inclined to say anything."
    },
    {
      "start": 215.34,
      "end": 216.08,
      "text": "\"Why,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 216.32,
      "end": 217.14,
      "text": "said the Dodo,"
    },
    {
      "start": 217.26,
      "end": 219.96,
      "text": "\"the best way to explain it is to do it.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 220.8,
      "end": 221.26,
      "text": "(And, as you"
    },
    {
      "start": 221.26,
      "end": 223.5,
      "text": "might like to try the thing yourself some winter day,"
    },
    {
      "start": 223.64,
      "end": 225.64,
      "text": "I will tell you how the Dodo managed it.)"
    },
    {
      "start": 226.32,
      "end": 226.92,
      "text": "First",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 227.06,
      "end": 229.4,
      "text": "it marked out a race-course, in a sort of circle,"
    },
    {
      "start": 230.08,
      "end": 231.68,
      "text": "(\"the exact shape doesn't matter,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 231.88,
      "end": 232.3,
      "text": "it said,)"
    },
    {
      "start": 232.8,
      "end": 235.86,
      "text": "and then all the party were placed along the course, here and there."
    },
    {
      "start": 236.54,
      "end": 237.72,
      "text": "There was no \"One,"
    },
    {
      "start": 237.9,
      "end": 238.1,
      "text": "two,"
    },
    {
      "start": 238.28,
      "end": 238.42,
      "text": "three,"
    },
    {
      "start": 238.58,
      "end": 239.04,
      "text": "and away,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 239.26,
      "end": 241.52,
      "text": "but they began running when they liked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 241.66,
      "end": 243.1,
      "text": "and left off when they liked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 243.2,
      "end": 245.84,
      "text": "so that it was not easy to know when the race was over."
    },
    {
      "start": 246.08,
      "end": 246.18,
      "text": "However,"
    },
    {
      "start": 247.22,
      "end": 248.5,
      "text": "when they had been running"
    },
    {
      "start": 248.58,
      "end": 249.68,
      "text": "half an hour or so,"
    },
    {
      "start": 249.82,
      "end": 251.1,
      "text": "and were quite dry again,"
    },
    {
      "start": 251.52,
      "end": 252.8,
      "text": "the Dodo suddenly called"
    },
    {
      "start": 253.34,
      "end": 254.28,
      "text": "\"The race is over!\""
    }
  ]
}